## Observability

OpenTelemetry instrumentation strategy:

- **Tracing:** Spans for all significant operations, end-to-end context propagation, relevant semantic attributes
- **Metrics:** Business counters and histograms, latencies per operation, errors by type
- **Logging:** Structured logs correlated with TraceID, appropriate levels (no logging of sensitive data)

{{OBSERVABILITY_STRATEGY}}

## Production Requirements

### Graceful Shutdown
- OS signal capture (SIGINT, SIGTERM)
- Stop accepting new requests, complete in-progress ones
- Close external connections, export pending telemetry
- Configurable timeout

### Health Checks
- Endpoint /health/live (liveness) and /health/ready (readiness)
- Critical dependency verification

### Resilience
- Retry with exponential backoff for transient operations
- Circuit breaker for external services
- Configurable timeouts on all operations

